          "management_commentary": "Moneyboxx Finance Limited achieved 27% AUM growth, reaching \u20b9927 crore, with disbursements of \u20b9595 crore. Total income grew by 55.69% to \u20b9199.23 crore. However, net profit declined to \u20b91.25 crore from \u20b99.14 crore in FY24, primarily due to increased credit costs. The company expanded its operations to 163 branches across 12 states and strengthened its 70+ member collections team. Financial position remained robust with a Capital Adequacy Ratio of 29.3% and a debt-to-equity ratio of 2.44x. Asset quality was managed prudently with GNPA at 6.6% and NNPA at 3.4%. The company leveraged co-lending partnerships and digital platforms like the Sikka app and an AI-led ecosystem for scalability and reach.",
          "key_risks": [
            "Challenging credit environment for the MSME segment, leading to a rise in delinquencies due to subdued rural growth, erratic weather patterns, and high indebtedness in certain borrower segments.",
            "Increased credit costs impacting net profit.",
            "Economic conditions, government policies, and other incidental factors beyond the control of the Company."
          ],
          "expansion_plans": "The company plans to scale AUM beyond \u20b91,400 crore in FY 2025-26 and increase the share of secured lending to 65% by March 2026. Key priorities include strengthening collections and legal recovery frameworks, accelerating technology-led initiatives such as Cattle AI and digital underwriting, and expanding co-lending partnerships and the lender ecosystem for greater balance-sheet strength. The company also targets achieving sub-10% opex within the next two years and a single-digit cost of funds in the next 2-3 years."
        },
